From: Cline <agent@local>
Date: Sat, 23 May 2026 20:05:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] PR14z22 step-1 DIAGNOSTIC: cc_v4_tcp miss_action FORWARD_FQ -> DROP

Temporary diagnostic patch to prove or disprove the CC-key-mismatch
hypothesis from plans/PR14z22-DESIGN.md.

Background: post-PR14z20 silicon regdump confirms the CC tree IS armed
(kgse_ccbs=0x0005ac00/0x0005ad00) and IS being walked during iperf3
(kgse_spc gained 37M classifications in 10s). But the M2 acceptance gate
still reports 52% softirq because every packet falls through cc_v4_tcp's
miss_action = FORWARD_FQ(dpaa_get_rx_default_fqid) -> the kernel's
NAPI-polled RX_DEFAULT FQ.

This patch flips the miss-action to DROP. Expected outcomes:

  - If throughput collapses to ~0 Gbps and ARP/SSH also fails: every
    packet was MISSing the CC lookup, confirming the key-layout mismatch.
    Next step is to read MURAM key bytes and compare against captured
    5-tuple from tcpdump.

  - If throughput stays >= 2 Gbps via the silicon HIT path: keys WERE
    matching; softirq came from a different source (QMan portal IRQ,
    NAPI poll on TX confirmation queues, etc.).

DESTRUCTIVE: this WILL drop ARP / SYN / ICMP / management traffic during
the test window. Run only with iperf3 from lxc201 -> lxc202 and panic=60
watchdog ready.

REVERT this patch before merging to main. It is staged under the highest
0053-* number and will be removed in the PR14z22 follow-up that lands the
actual fix once the hypothesis is confirmed.

Signed-off-by: Cline <agent@local>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/ask/ask_hw.c | 10 ++++++++--
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/ask/ask_hw.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/ask/ask_hw.c
index dc41947..d82a7ae 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/ask/ask_hw.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/ask/ask_hw.c
@@ -997,8 +997,14 @@ int ask_hw_port_bind(u8 port_id, enum ask_hw_dir dir,
         memset(&keys, 0, sizeof(keys));
         keys.num_keys = 127;  /* PR14z5 hotfix: 127 per pipeline (MURAM budget) */
         keys.keys = NULL;
-        keys.miss_action.type             = FMAN_PCD_ACTION_FORWARD_FQ;
-        keys.miss_action.forward_fq.fqid  = base_fqid;
+        /*
+         * PR14z22 step-1 DIAGNOSTIC: drop miss-action target instead of
+         * falling through to kernel RX_DEFAULT FQ.  If the CC keys ARE
+         * matching, iperf3 stays high; if they are NOT matching, throughput
+         * collapses to ~0.  Revert before merging to main.
+         */
+        keys.miss_action.type = FMAN_PCD_ACTION_DROP;
+        (void)base_fqid;  /* suppress unused-var warning */
 
         new_node = fman_pcd_cc_node_create(p->cc_tree, &extract, &keys);
         if (IS_ERR_OR_NULL(new_node)) {
